This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for identifying missing articles and ranking them according to their importance. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for recommending articles to editors based on their interests, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves network analysis and graph algorithms for identifying missing articles, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of Computational Geometry (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves deep learning (DL) techniques for modeling editor interests and article importance, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.DL).
